\fs18 \cf4 \cb31 \strokec4 The first time he cooked, he nearly set the stove on fire. Among those who rushed to help was a chef who, looking at the pile of burnt food, used the unused eggs to make him a plate of fried rice.\cb1 \
\cb31 He wolfed it down with tears in his eyes. When he finally looked up, the cook was holding out a slip of paper with "100" written on it.\cb1 \
\cb31 "I understand, Master! You're teaching me in cooking, you have to give it 100%, right?" "No, I'm saying it's 100 Dennies per bite, and you've had over a hundred bites. Time to pay up."\cb1 \
\cb31 From that day on, Pan Yinhu insisted on cooking for himself and never messed up again. And that's how a first-class chef was born.\cb1 \
